'''Yamato no Iotari''' was [[:en:Japanese nobility|an aristocrat]] from {{ill|Asuka period|en|Asuka period|WD=Q210688|lt=the Asuka period|1=Asuka period}} to {{ill|Nara period|en|Nara period|WD=Q189178|lt=the Nara period|1=Nara period}} . His {{ill|Kabane|en|Kabane|WD=Q1664099|lt=Kabane|1=Kabane}} was {{ill|10=ja|11=ň┐îň»Ş|Ikisui|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=}} . His {{ill|List of Japanese court ranks, positions and hereditary titles|en|List of Japanese court ranks, positions and hereditary titles|WD=Q11452077|lt=official Rank|1=List of Japanese court ranks, positions and hereditary titles}} was {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank|ja|ňżôń║öńŻŹ|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}} and his job was {{ill|10=ja|11=f|Ministry_of_Justice_(pre-modern_Japan)|en|lt=Junior Assistant Minister of Justice|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=}} .

He served under {{ill|Emperor Monmu|en|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Monmu|qq=}}, [[:en:Empress Gemmei|Empress Gemmei]], {{ill|Empress Gensh┼Ź|en|Empress Gensh┼Ź|WD=Q235343|lt=Empress Gensh┼Ź|1=Empress Gensh┼Ź}}, and {{ill|Emperor Sh┼Źmu|en|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Sh┼Źmu|qq=}}.

